summary:
Hi!
My name is Ekaterina and I am a C# developer.

About me:
I am currently working in a healthcare industry as a C# developer. Also I have gained interesting experience in developing applications for interacting with Ouster lidars, and also participated in the development of a video number recognition system.
I want to develop further, gain new experience in team development in modern progressive companies.

Technologies:

C# stack :

- write on a framework ASP.NET core;
- have experience in developing web api, WPF applications;
- implemented full-stack projects using React Js, TypeScript, hooks, redux-toolkit;
- worked with a database (MS SQL Express or postgresql) using Entity Framework;
- linq, AutoMapper, REST, Moq.

python stack:

- pandas, matplotlib, numpy, see

English Level: IELTS Certificate: 7 (advanced).

school.name: Peter the Great St.Petersburg Polytechnic University

profile_positions.description:
Medindex is a software development company in the healthcare industry. Our team is engaged in the preparation and sending of test results to the clients of the Helix laboratory service.

I managed to take part in strategic projects: the transition from a monolith project with a third-party engine for generating PDF reports to our own microservices and engine; the translation of analysis results into Kazakh for sampling sites in Kazakhstan.

In this position, I am actively learning to be part of a team. We practice code review, discuss various approaches of solving the problem, monitor the quality of the code base. I am often the host of team calls and meetings, and I try to be active in communication with my colleagues.
profile_positions.title: Software Engineer

profile_positions.description:
I managed to implement two independent projects for setting up Oyster lidars (https://ouster.com).
The  "Automation" company is engaged in the supply of special dimensional frames for railway tracks in Russia and CIS countries to ensure quality control of transportation of bulky goods.

My task was to facilitate the work of the installation engineers.

One of the projects was an application with a simple and intuitive interface for network configuration of a lidar - port and address transfer, for connection between a PC and a device, it was also possible to configure the lidar's characteristics - the number of revolutions per second, viewing angle, etc.

The second project implemented the possibility of configuring three lidars in parallel. The task was to combine point clouds from each lidar to obtain a complete dynamic 3D picture of a moving car. In this task, I used the knowledge gained at the university - rotation and shift matrices.

In this position, I learned to read the documentation in a foreign language to understand the operation of the device. I also got great pleasure from communicating with real engineers, managed to make friends with the team and learn from professionals in their field.
profile_positions.title: Инженер-программист
